                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18230409-153-off809 t18230409-153-crimeloc811"></join>. On the 19th of March, the prisoner lodged at my house; I missed my coat and trowsers, they were safe the day before; I found him with them on the next day; I had lent them to him several Sunday's to appear decent in; I asked why he took them, he said; he intended to return them; he was never out of the house a night before; he said he had been to a dance.</p>
               <p>Prisoner's Defence. I had no idea of stealing them, he had lent them to me several times, and I had often put them on without asking leave.</p>
